This bug is about diagnostic output quality in `dump_cpu_task()` — it improves the register display during RCU stall detection on non-NMI architectures (ARM64/RISC-V). On x86 (which kSTEP uses), `trigger_single_cpu_backtrace()` via NMI already works, making both buggy and fixed kernels produce useful output. Additionally, triggering RCU stalls requires real hardirq context, which kSTEP's controlled tick mechanism doesn't provide. This is not reproducible with kSTEP.

